Function: rmse

rmse <- function(truedata, imp, variable) {
  mx <- is.na(mice::complete(imp, 0))[, variable]
  mse <- rep(NA, imp$m)
  for (k in seq_len(imp$m)) {
    filled <- mice::complete(imp, k)[mx, variable]
    true <- truedata[mx, variable]
    mse[k] <- mean((filled - true)^2)
  }
  sqrt(mean(mse))
}

Function: Creating simulations

set.seed(444)
# Number of simulations
nsim = 500

# Defining 4 missingness patterns
mypatterns <- rbind(c(1,0,0,1,1,1,1,1,1), #pattern1
                    c(1,1,1,0,0,1,1,1,1), #pattern2
                    c(1,1,1,1,0,0,1,1,1), #pattern3
                    c(1,0,0,1,1,1,1,1,1)) #pattern4

simulate <- function(complete.data, p){
  
  data <- complete.data
  
  #Bootstrapping the data
  boot <- data[sample(1:nrow(data), nrow(data), replace = TRUE), ]

  # Creating missingness
  missing <- ampute(boot, prop = p, patterns = mypatterns,
                    mech = "MCAR")$amp
  
  #imputation methods
  imp.mean <- mice(missing, method = "mean", m = 1, maxit = 1, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.reg <- mice(missing, method = "norm.predict", m = 1, maxit = 1, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.stoch.m1 <- mice(missing, method = "norm.nob", m = 1, maxit = 7, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.stoch.m5 <- mice(missing, method = "norm.nob", m = 5, maxit = 7, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.bayes.m1 <- mice(missing, method = "norm", m = 1, maxit = 7, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.bayes.m5 <- mice(missing, method = "norm", m = 5, maxit = 7, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.pmm.m1 <- mice(missing, method = "pmm", m = 1, maxit = 7, printFlag = FALSE)
  imp.pmm.m5 <- mice(missing, method = "pmm", m = 5, maxit = 7, printFlag = FALSE)

  #RMSE y 
   rmse.mean.y <- rmse(boot, imp.mean, "BMI")
   rmse.reg.y <- rmse(boot, imp.reg, "BMI")
   rmse.stochm1.y <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m1, "BMI")
   rmse.stochm5.y <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m5, "BMI")
   rmse.bayesm1.y <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m1, "BMI")
   rmse.bayesm5.y <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m5, "BMI")
   rmse.pmmm1.y <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m1, "BMI")
   rmse.pmmm5.y <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m5, "BMI")
  
  #RMSE x1 
   rmse.mean.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.mean, "Glucose")
   rmse.reg.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.reg, "Glucose")
   rmse.stochm1.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m1, "Glucose")
   rmse.stochm5.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m5, "Glucose")
   rmse.bayesm1.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m1, "Glucose")
   rmse.bayesm5.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m5, "Glucose")
   rmse.pmmm1.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m1, "Glucose")
   rmse.pmmm5.x1 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m5, "Glucose")
   
   #RMSE x2
   rmse.mean.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.mean, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.reg.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.reg, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.stochm1.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m1, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.stochm5.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m5, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.bayesm1.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m1, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.bayesm5.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m5, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.pmmm1.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m1, "BloodPressure")
   rmse.pmmm5.x2 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m5, "BloodPressure")
   
   #RMSE x3
   rmse.mean.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.mean, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.reg.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.reg, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.stochm1.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m1, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.stochm5.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m5, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.bayesm1.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m1, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.bayesm5.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m5, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.pmmm1.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m1, "SkinThickness")
   rmse.pmmm5.x3 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m5, "SkinThickness")
   
   #RMSE x4
   rmse.mean.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.mean, "Insulin")
   rmse.reg.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.reg, "Insulin")
   rmse.stochm1.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m1, "Insulin")
   rmse.stochm5.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.stoch.m5, "Insulin")
   rmse.bayesm1.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m1, "Insulin")
   rmse.bayesm5.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.bayes.m5, "Insulin")
   rmse.pmmm1.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m1, "Insulin")
   rmse.pmmm5.x4 <- rmse(boot, imp.pmm.m5, "Insulin")
   
 
  #Returning list with results
  return(list(imp.mean = imp.mean,  imp.reg = imp.reg, imp.stoch.m1 = imp.stoch.m1,
               imp.stoch.m5 = imp.stoch.m5, imp.bayes.m1 = imp.bayes.m1,
               imp.bayes.m5 = imp.bayes.m5, imp.pmm.m1 = imp.pmm.m1,
               imp.pmm.m5 = imp.pmm.m5, data = complete.data, boot = boot,
              rmse.mean.y = rmse.mean.y, rmse.mean.x1 = rmse.mean.x1, rmse.mean.x2 = rmse.mean.x2, rmse.mean.x3 = rmse.mean.x3, rmse.mean.x4 = rmse.mean.x4,
              rmse.reg.y = rmse.reg.y, rmse.reg.x1 = rmse.reg.x1, rmse.reg.x2 = rmse.reg.x2, rmse.reg.x3 = rmse.reg.x3, rmse.reg.x4 = rmse.reg.x4,
              rmse.stochm1.y = rmse.stochm1.y, rmse.stochm1.x1 = rmse.stochm1.x1, rmse.stochm1.x2 = rmse.stochm1.x2, rmse.stochm1.x3 = rmse.stochm1.x3, rmse.stochm1.x4 = rmse.stochm1.x4,
              rmse.stochm5.y = rmse.stochm5.y, rmse.stochm5.x1 = rmse.stochm5.x1, rmse.stochm5.x2 = rmse.stochm5.x2, rmse.stochm5.x3 = rmse.stochm5.x3, rmse.stochm5.x4 = rmse.stochm5.x4,
              rmse.bayesm1.y = rmse.bayesm1.y, rmse.bayesm1.x1 = rmse.bayesm1.x1, rmse.bayesm1.x2 = rmse.bayesm1.x2, rmse.bayesm1.x3 = rmse.bayesm1.x3, rmse.bayesm1.x4 = rmse.bayesm1.x4,
              rmse.bayesm5.y = rmse.bayesm5.y, rmse.bayesm5.x1 = rmse.bayesm5.x1, rmse.bayesm5.x2 = rmse.bayesm5.x2, rmse.bayesm5.x3 = rmse.bayesm5.x3, rmse.bayesm5.x4 = rmse.bayesm5.x4,
              rmse.pmmm1.y = rmse.pmmm1.y, rmse.pmmm1.x1 = rmse.pmmm1.x1, rmse.pmmm1.x2 = rmse.pmmm1.x2, rmse.pmmm1.x3 = rmse.pmmm1.x3, rmse.pmmm1.x4 = rmse.pmmm1.x4,
              rmse.pmmm5.y = rmse.pmmm5.y, rmse.pmmm5.x1 = rmse.pmmm5.x1, rmse.pmmm5.x2 = rmse.pmmm5.x2, rmse.pmmm5.x3 = rmse.pmmm5.x3, rmse.pmmm5.x4 = rmse.pmmm5.x4
              )) 
}
  
# Run simulation
result.p50 <- replicate(nsim, simulate(data, 0.5), simplify = FALSE)
result.p25 <- replicate(nsim, simulate(data, 0.25), simplify = FALSE)
result.p10 <- replicate(nsim, simulate(data, 0.10), simplify = FALSE)

truemodel <- data %$% 
  lm(BMI ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin) %>% 
  coef()

# Fitting the predictors as the outcome variable.
truedata.fit.x1y <- lm(Glucose ~ BMI + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = data)$coefficients

Function: grab results

# Function for grabbing the results for multiple imputation methods
grab.it <- function(x){
  model <- x %>% 
    map(~.x %>%
        complete("all") %>%
        map(~.x %$%
              lm(BMI ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin)) %>%
        pool())
  estim <- model %>%
        map(~.x %>% summary() %>% .$estimate) %>%
        do.call(rbind, args = .)
  model %>%
  map(~.x %>% .$pooled %>%
        mutate(se = sqrt(diag(var(estim))),
               lower = estimate - qt(.975, df) * se,
               upper = estimate + qt(.975, df) * se,
               bias = estimate - truemodel,
               CIW = upper - lower,
               coverage = lower <= truemodel & truemodel <= upper) %>% 
              column_to_rownames(var = "term")) %>%
    Reduce("+", .) / nsim
}


# Function for grabbing the results for single imputation methods
grab.it.single <- function(x){
  model <- x %>% 
    map(~.x %>%
          complete("all") %>%
          map(~.x %$%  
                lm(BMI ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin)) %>% 
          pool())
  estim <- model %>% 
    map(~.x %>% coefficients()) %>% 
    do.call(rbind, args = .)
  df <- model[[1]]$df.residual
  model %>% map(~.x %>% summary() %>% .$coefficients %>% as.data.frame() %>% 
        mutate(se = sqrt(diag(var(estim))),
               lower = Estimate - qt(.975, df) * se,
               upper = Estimate + qt(.975, df) * se,
               bias = Estimate - truemodel,
               CIW = upper - lower,
               coverage = lower <= truemodel & truemodel <= upper)) %>% 
    Reduce("+", .) / nsim
}

Function: reverse model regression coefficients (true values) - Bias.

true.estimates.p <- function(x) {

      fit <- lm(BMI ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = x)
      summary <- summary(fit, conf.int = TRUE)

      #betas
      x1.beta <- fit$coefficients["Glucose"]
      x2.beta <- fit$coefficients["BloodPressure"]
      x3.beta <- fit$coefficients["SkinThickness"]
      x4.beta <- fit$coefficients["Insulin"]

      
      #standard errors
      x1.beta.se <- summary$coefficients["Glucose", "Std. Error"]
      x2.beta.se <- summary$coefficients["BloodPressure", "Std. Error"]
      x3.beta.se <- summary$coefficients["SkinThickness", "Std. Error"]
      x4.beta.se <- summary$coefficients["Insulin", "Std. Error"]

      #CI low 
      x1.beta.CI.low <-  confint(fit)[2,1]
      x2.beta.CI.low  <- confint(fit)[3,1]
      x3.beta.CI.low  <- confint(fit)[4,1]
      x4.beta.CI.low  <- confint(fit)[5,1]
      
      #CI high
      x1.beta.CI.high <-  confint(fit)[2,2]
      x2.beta.CI.high  <- confint(fit)[3,2]
      x3.beta.CI.high  <- confint(fit)[4,2]
      x4.beta.CI.high  <- confint(fit)[5,2]
      
      # AW
      x1.beta.aw <- x1.beta.CI.high - x1.beta.CI.low
      x2.beta.aw <- x2.beta.CI.high - x2.beta.CI.low
      x3.beta.aw <- x3.beta.CI.high - x3.beta.CI.low
      x4.beta.aw <- x4.beta.CI.high - x4.beta.CI.low
      
      #bias
      x1.beta.bias <- 0
      x2.beta.bias <- 0
      x3.beta.bias <- 0
      x4.beta.bias <- 0
      
      #coverage 
      x1.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      x2.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      x3.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      x4.beta.coverage <- FALSE
       
      r.squared <- summary$r.squared
      
      #reversed models
      fit.x1y <- lm(Glucose ~ BMI + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = x)
      fit.x2y <- lm(BloodPressure ~ Glucose + BMI + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = x)
      fit.x3y <- lm(SkinThickness ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + BMI + Insulin, data = x)
      fit.x4y <- lm(Insulin ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + BMI, data = x)
   
      #summaries
      summary.x1y <- summ(fit.x1y, confint = TRUE)
      summary.x2y <- summ(fit.x2y, confint = TRUE)
      summary.x3y <- summ(fit.x3y, confint = TRUE)
      summary.x4y <- summ(fit.x4y, confint = TRUE)

      #betas
      x1y.beta <- fit.x1y$coefficients["BMI"]
      x2y.beta <- fit.x2y$coefficients["BMI"]
      x3y.beta <- fit.x3y$coefficients["BMI"]
      x4y.beta <- fit.x4y$coefficients["BMI"]
      
      #standard errors
      x1y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x1y)$coefficients[2,2]
      x2y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x2y)$coefficients[3,2]
      x3y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x3y)$coefficients[4,2]
      x4y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x4y)$coefficients[5,2]
   
      #CI low 
      x1y.beta.CI.low <- summary.x1y$coeftable[2,2]
      x2y.beta.CI.low  <- summary.x2y$coeftable[3,2]
      x3y.beta.CI.low  <- summary.x3y$coeftable[4,2]
      x4y.beta.CI.low  <- summary.x4y$coeftable[5,2]
      
      #CI high
      x1y.beta.CI.high <- summary.x1y$coeftable[2,3]
      x2y.beta.CI.high  <- summary.x2y$coeftable[3,3]
      x3y.beta.CI.high  <- summary.x3y$coeftable[4,3]
      x4y.beta.CI.high  <- summary.x4y$coeftable[5,3]
      
      # AW
      x1y.beta.aw <- x1y.beta.CI.high - x1y.beta.CI.low
      x2y.beta.aw <- x2y.beta.CI.high - x2y.beta.CI.low
      x3y.beta.aw <- x3y.beta.CI.high - x3y.beta.CI.low
      x4y.beta.aw <- x4y.beta.CI.high - x4y.beta.CI.low
  
      #bias
      x1y.beta.bias <- 0
      x2y.beta.bias <- 0
      x3y.beta.bias <- 0
      x4y.beta.bias <- 0
        
      #coverage 
      x1y.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      x2y.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      x3y.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      x4y.beta.coverage <- FALSE
      

  return(c(x1.beta, x1.beta.se, x1.beta.bias, x1.beta.aw, x1.beta.coverage, r.squared,
           x2.beta, x2.beta.se, x2.beta.bias, x2.beta.aw, x2.beta.coverage,
           x3.beta, x3.beta.se, x3.beta.bias, x3.beta.aw, x3.beta.coverage,
           x4.beta, x4.beta.se, x4.beta.bias, x4.beta.aw, x4.beta.coverage,
           x1y.beta, x1y.beta.se, x1y.beta.bias, x1y.beta.aw, x1y.beta.coverage,
           x2y.beta, x2y.beta.se, x2y.beta.bias, x2y.beta.aw, x2y.beta.coverage, 
           x3y.beta, x3y.beta.se, x3y.beta.bias, x3y.beta.aw, x3y.beta.coverage, 
           x4y.beta, x4y.beta.se, x4y.beta.bias, x4y.beta.aw, x4y.beta.coverage))
}

Function: reverse model regression coefficients (imputations) - Bias.

statistics.p <- function(x) {
   
   m <- x$m # Amount of imputations
   
   #  Get the truedata from the global environment
   truedata.fit <- get("truemodel", envir = .GlobalEnv)
   truedata.x1y <- get("truedata.fit.x1y", envir = .GlobalEnv)
   truedata.x2y <- get("truedata.fit.x2y", envir = .GlobalEnv)
   truedata.x3y <- get("truedata.fit.x3y", envir = .GlobalEnv)
   truedata.x4y <- get("truedata.fit.x4y", envir = .GlobalEnv)
   
   # multiple imputation analysis
   if (m > 1) {
      
      fit <- with(x, lm(BMI ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin))
      est <- pool(fit)
      summary <- summary(est, conf.int = TRUE)

      
      # Betas
      x1.beta <- summary$estimate[2] # Glucose
      x2.beta <- summary$estimate[3] # BloodPressure
      x3.beta <- summary$estimate[4] # SkinThickness
      x4.beta <- summary$estimate[5] # Insulin
      
      # SE
      x1.beta.se <- summary$std.error[2]
      x2.beta.se <- summary$std.error[3]
      x3.beta.se <- summary$std.error[4]
      x4.beta.se <- summary$std.error[5]
              
      # Confidence interval low
      x1.beta.CI.low <- summary  %>% filter(term == "Glucose") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x2.beta.CI.low <- summary  %>% filter(term == "BloodPressure") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x3.beta.CI.low <- summary  %>% filter(term == "SkinThickness") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x4.beta.CI.low <- summary  %>% filter(term == "Insulin") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      
      # Confidence interval high
      x1.beta.CI.high <- summary %>% filter(term == "Glucose") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x2.beta.CI.high <- summary %>% filter(term == "BloodPressure") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x3.beta.CI.high <- summary %>% filter(term == "SkinThickness") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x4.beta.CI.high <- summary %>% filter(term == "Insulin") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      
      # Average width 
      x1.beta.aw <- x1.beta.CI.high - x1.beta.CI.low
      x2.beta.aw <- x2.beta.CI.high - x2.beta.CI.low
      x3.beta.aw <- x3.beta.CI.high - x3.beta.CI.low
      x4.beta.aw <- x4.beta.CI.high - x4.beta.CI.low
  
      # Raw bias
      x1.beta.bias <- x1.beta - truedata.fit["Glucose"]
      x2.beta.bias <- x2.beta - truedata.fit["BloodPressure"]
      x3.beta.bias <- x3.beta - truedata.fit["SkinThickness"]
      x4.beta.bias <- x4.beta - truedata.fit["Insulin"]
                              
      # Coverage rate
      x1.beta.coverage <- x1.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["Glucose"] & truedata.fit["Glucose"] < x1.beta.CI.high
      x2.beta.coverage <- x2.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["BloodPressure"] & truedata.fit["BloodPressure"] < x2.beta.CI.high
      x3.beta.coverage <- x3.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["SkinThickness"] & truedata.fit["SkinThickness"] < x3.beta.CI.high
      x4.beta.coverage <- x4.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["Insulin"] & truedata.fit["Insulin"] < x4.beta.CI.high
   
       # R2
      r.squared <- pool.r.squared(est, adjusted = FALSE)[[1]]
      
      # Reversing the predictor, x as outcome
      fit.x1y <- with(x, lm(Glucose ~ BMI + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin)) #Glucose as outcome
      fit.x2y <- with(x, lm(BloodPressure ~ Glucose + BMI + SkinThickness + Insulin)) #Bloodpressure as outcome
      fit.x3y <- with(x, lm(SkinThickness ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + BMI + Insulin)) #SkinThickness as outcome
      fit.x4y <- with(x, lm(Insulin ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + BMI)) #SkinThickness as outcome
      
      # Pooling the new models
      est.x1y <- pool(fit.x1y)
      est.x2y <- pool(fit.x2y)
      est.x3y <- pool(fit.x3y)
      est.x4y <- pool(fit.x4y)
      
      # Summaries of models
      summary.x1y <- summary(est.x1y, conf.int = TRUE)
      summary.x2y <- summary(est.x2y, conf.int = TRUE) 
      summary.x3y <- summary(est.x3y, conf.int = TRUE)
      summary.x4y <- summary(est.x4y, conf.int = TRUE) 
   
      # Betas of Y BMI as predictor in reversed models
      x1y.beta <- est.x1y$pooled$estimate[2]
      x2y.beta <- est.x2y$pooled$estimate[3]
      x3y.beta <- est.x3y$pooled$estimate[4]
      x4y.beta <- est.x4y$pooled$estimate[5]
      
      # SE
      x1y.beta.se <- summary.x1y$std.error[2]
      x2y.beta.se <- summary.x2y$std.error[3]
      x3y.beta.se <- summary.x3y$std.error[4]
      x4y.beta.se <- summary.x4y$std.error[5]
      
      # CI LOW
      x1y.beta.CI.low <- summary.x1y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x2y.beta.CI.low <- summary.x2y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x3y.beta.CI.low <- summary.x3y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x4y.beta.CI.low <- summary.x4y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`2.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      
      # CI High
      x1y.beta.CI.high <- summary.x1y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x2y.beta.CI.high <- summary.x2y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x3y.beta.CI.high <- summary.x3y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
      x4y.beta.CI.high <- summary.x4y  %>% filter(term == "BMI") %>% select(c(`97.5 %`)) %>% unlist()
    
      # AW
      x1y.beta.aw <- x1y.beta.CI.high - x1y.beta.CI.low
      x2y.beta.aw <- x2y.beta.CI.high - x2y.beta.CI.low
      x3y.beta.aw <- x3y.beta.CI.high - x3y.beta.CI.low
      x4y.beta.aw <- x4y.beta.CI.high - x4y.beta.CI.low
      
      # BIAS
      x1y.beta.bias <- x1y.beta - truedata.fit.x1y["BMI"]
      x2y.beta.bias <- x2y.beta - truedata.fit.x2y["BMI"]
      x3y.beta.bias <- x3y.beta - truedata.fit.x3y["BMI"]
      x4y.beta.bias <- x4y.beta - truedata.fit.x4y["BMI"]
      
      
      # Coverage rate
      x1y.beta.coverage <- x1y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x1y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x1y["BMI"] < x1y.beta.CI.high
      x2y.beta.coverage <- x2y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x2y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x2y["BMI"] < x2y.beta.CI.high
      x3y.beta.coverage <- x3y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x3y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x3y["BMI"] < x3y.beta.CI.high
      x4y.beta.coverage <- x4y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x4y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x4y["BMI"] < x4y.beta.CI.high
   
   }

    # single imputation analysis
   else {
   
      mids <- complete(x, action = "all") #mids
      fit <- mids %>% map(~lm(BMI ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = .)) %>% .[[1]]
      summary <- summ(fit, confint = TRUE)
      
      
      #betas
      x1.beta <- fit$coefficients["Glucose"]
      x2.beta <- fit$coefficients["BloodPressure"]
      x3.beta <- fit$coefficients["SkinThickness"]
      x4.beta <- fit$coefficients["Insulin"]
   
      
      #standard errors
      x1.beta.se <- summary(fit)$coefficients[2,2]
      x2.beta.se <- summary(fit)$coefficients[3,2]
      x3.beta.se <- summary(fit)$coefficients[4,2]
      x4.beta.se <- summary(fit)$coefficients[5,2]
      
      #CI low 
      x1.beta.CI.low <- summary$coeftable[2,2]
      x2.beta.CI.low  <- summary$coeftable[3,2]
      x3.beta.CI.low  <- summary$coeftable[4,2]
      x4.beta.CI.low  <- summary$coeftable[5,2]
      
      #CI high
      x1.beta.CI.high <- summary$coeftable[2,3]
      x2.beta.CI.high  <- summary$coeftable[3,3]
      x3.beta.CI.high  <- summary$coeftable[4,3]
      x4.beta.CI.high  <- summary$coeftable[5,3]
  
      #bias
      x1.beta.bias <- x1.beta - truedata.fit["Glucose"]
      x2.beta.bias <- x2.beta - truedata.fit["BloodPressure"]
      x3.beta.bias <- x3.beta - truedata.fit["SkinThickness"]
      x4.beta.bias <- x4.beta - truedata.fit["Insulin"]
      
      #Aw
      x1.beta.aw <- x1.beta.CI.high - x1.beta.CI.low
      x2.beta.aw <- x2.beta.CI.high - x2.beta.CI.low
      x3.beta.aw <- x3.beta.CI.high - x3.beta.CI.low
      x4.beta.aw <- x4.beta.CI.high - x4.beta.CI.low
      
      #coverage 
      x1.beta.coverage <- x1.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["Glucose"] & truedata.fit["Glucose"] < x1.beta.CI.high
      x2.beta.coverage <- x2.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["BloodPressure"] & truedata.fit["BloodPressure"] < x2.beta.CI.high
      x3.beta.coverage <- x3.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["SkinThickness"] & truedata.fit["SkinThickness"] < x3.beta.CI.high
      x4.beta.coverage <- x4.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit["Insulin"] & truedata.fit["Insulin"] < x4.beta.CI.high
       
      r.squared <- summary(fit)$r.squared
      
      #reversed models
      fit.x1y <- mids %>% map(~lm(Glucose ~ BMI + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = .x)) %>% .[[1]]
      fit.x2y <- mids %>% map(~lm(BloodPressure ~ Glucose + BMI + SkinThickness + Insulin, data = .x)) %>% .[[1]]
      fit.x3y <- mids %>% map(~lm(SkinThickness ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + BMI + Insulin, data = .x)) %>% .[[1]]
      fit.x4y <- mids %>% map(~lm(Insulin ~ Glucose + BloodPressure + SkinThickness + BMI, data = .x)) %>% .[[1]]
      
      #summaries
      summary.x1y <- summ(fit.x1y, confint = TRUE)
      summary.x2y <- summ(fit.x2y, confint = TRUE)
      summary.x3y <- summ(fit.x3y, confint = TRUE)
      summary.x4y <- summ(fit.x4y, confint = TRUE)

      #betas
      x1y.beta <- fit.x1y$coefficients["BMI"]
      x2y.beta <- fit.x2y$coefficients["BMI"]
      x3y.beta <- fit.x3y$coefficients["BMI"]
      x4y.beta <- fit.x4y$coefficients["BMI"]
      
      #standard errors
      x1y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x1y)$coefficients[2,2]
      x2y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x2y)$coefficients[3,2]
      x3y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x3y)$coefficients[4,2]
      x4y.beta.se <- summary(fit.x4y)$coefficients[5,2]
   
      #CI low 
      x1y.beta.CI.low <- summary.x1y$coeftable[2,2]
      x2y.beta.CI.low  <- summary.x2y$coeftable[3,2]
      x3y.beta.CI.low  <- summary.x3y$coeftable[4,2]
      x4y.beta.CI.low  <- summary.x4y$coeftable[5,2]
      
      #CI high
      x1y.beta.CI.high <- summary.x1y$coeftable[2,3]
      x2y.beta.CI.high  <- summary.x2y$coeftable[3,3]
      x3y.beta.CI.high  <- summary.x3y$coeftable[4,3]
      x4y.beta.CI.high  <- summary.x4y$coeftable[5,3]
  
      #bias
      x1y.beta.bias <- x1y.beta - truedata.fit.x1y["BMI"]
      x2y.beta.bias <- x2y.beta - truedata.fit.x2y["BMI"]
      x3y.beta.bias <- x3y.beta - truedata.fit.x3y["BMI"]
      x4y.beta.bias <- x4y.beta - truedata.fit.x4y["BMI"]
      
      # aw
      x1y.beta.aw <- x1y.beta.CI.high - x1y.beta.CI.low
      x2y.beta.aw <- x2y.beta.CI.high - x2y.beta.CI.low
      x3y.beta.aw <- x3y.beta.CI.high - x3y.beta.CI.low
      x4y.beta.aw <- x4y.beta.CI.high - x4y.beta.CI.low
      
      #coverage 
      x1y.beta.coverage <- x1y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x1y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x1y["BMI"] < x1y.beta.CI.high
      x2y.beta.coverage <- x2y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x2y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x2y["BMI"] < x2y.beta.CI.high
      x3y.beta.coverage <- x3y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x3y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x3y["BMI"] < x3y.beta.CI.high
      x4y.beta.coverage <- x4y.beta.CI.low < truedata.fit.x4y["BMI"] & truedata.fit.x4y["BMI"] < x4y.beta.CI.high

   }
      
    return(c(  x1.beta, x1.beta.se, x1.beta.bias, x1.beta.aw, x1.beta.coverage, r.squared,
               x2.beta, x2.beta.se, x2.beta.bias, x2.beta.aw, x2.beta.coverage,
               x3.beta, x3.beta.se, x3.beta.bias, x3.beta.aw, x3.beta.coverage,
               x4.beta, x4.beta.se, x4.beta.bias, x4.beta.aw, x4.beta.coverage,
               x1y.beta, x1y.beta.se, x1y.beta.bias, x1y.beta.aw, x1y.beta.coverage,
               x2y.beta, x2y.beta.se, x2y.beta.bias, x2y.beta.aw, x2y.beta.coverage, 
               x3y.beta, x3y.beta.se, x3y.beta.bias, x3y.beta.aw, x3y.beta.coverage, 
               x4y.beta, x4y.beta.se, x4y.beta.bias, x4y.beta.aw, x4y.beta.coverage))
}

Function: Descriptives (true values)

true.estimates.d <- function(x) {
   
   # Y - BMI
   y.mean <- mean(x$BMI)
   y.se <- sd(x$BMI) %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(x)))
   y.interval <- qt(.975, (sqrt(nrow(x)) - 1)) * y.se
   y.lower <- y.mean - y.interval
   y.upper <- y.mean + y.interval
   y.aw <- 0
   y.coverage <- 0
   y.bias <- 0
   
   # X1  variable - BMI
   x1.mean <- mean(x$Glucose)
   x1.se <- sd(x$Glucose) %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(x)))
   x1.interval <- qt(.975, (sqrt(nrow(x)) - 1)) * y.se
   x1.lower <- y.mean - y.interval
   x1.upper <- y.mean + y.interval
   x1.aw <- 0
   x1.coverage <- 0
   x1.bias <- 0

   # X2 variable - BMI
   x2.mean <- mean(x$BloodPressure)
   x2.se <- sd(x$BloodPressure) %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(x)))
   x2.interval <- qt(.975, (sqrt(nrow(x)) - 1)) * y.se
   x2.lower <- y.mean - y.interval
   x2.upper <- y.mean + y.interval
   x2.aw <- 0
   x2.coverage <- 0
   x2.bias <- 0

    # X3 variable - BMI
   x3.mean <- mean(x$SkinThickness)
   x3.se <- sd(x$SkinThickness) %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(x)))
   x3.interval <- qt(.975, (sqrt(nrow(x)) - 1)) * y.se
   x3.lower <- y.mean - y.interval
   x3.upper <- y.mean + y.interval
   x3.aw <- 0
   x3.coverage <- 0
   x3.bias <- 0

   # X4 variable - BMI
   x4.mean <- mean(x$Insulin)
   x4.se <- sd(x$Insulin) %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(x)))
   x4.interval <- qt(.975, (sqrt(nrow(x)) - 1)) * y.se
   x4.lower <- y.mean - y.interval
   x4.upper <- y.mean + y.interval
   x4.aw <- 0
   x4.coverage <- 0
   x4.bias <- 0
   
  return(c(y.mean, y.se, y.aw, y.coverage, y.bias,
           x1.mean, x1.se, x1.aw, x1.coverage, x1.bias,
           x2.mean, x2.se, x2.aw, x2.coverage, x2.bias,
           x3.mean, x3.se, x3.aw, x3.coverage, x3.bias,
           x4.mean, x4.se, x4.aw, x4.coverage, x4.bias))
}


format.d<- (c("y.mean" = 0," y.se" = 0, "y.aw" = 0, "y.coverage" = 0, "y.bias" = 0,
           "x1.mean" = 0, "x1.se" = 0, "x1.aw" = 0, "x1.coverage" = 0," x1.bias" = 0,
           "x2.mean" = 0, "x2.se" = 0, "x2.aw" = 0, "x2.coverage" = 0," x2.bias" = 0,
           "x3.mean" = 0, "x3.se" = 0, "x3.aw" = 0, "x3.coverage" = 0," x3.bias" = 0,
           "x4.mean" = 0, "x4.se" = 0, "x4.aw" = 0, "x4.coverage" = 0," x4.bias" = 0))

Function: Descriptives (imputations)

statistics.d <- function(x) {
   
   truedata <- get("data", envir = .GlobalEnv)
   mids <- complete(x, action = "all")
   
   # True values
   y.true <- truedata$BMI %>% mean()
   x1.true <- truedata$Glucose %>% mean()
   x2.true <- truedata$BloodPressure %>% mean()
   x3.true <- truedata$SkinThickness %>% mean()
   x4.true <- truedata$Insulin %>% mean()
     
   #Mean
   y.mean <- mids %>% map_df(~mean(.$BMI)) %>% t() %>% mean()
   x1.mean <- mids %>% map_df(~mean(.$Glucose)) %>% t() %>% mean()
   x2.mean <- mids %>% map_df(~mean(.$BloodPressure)) %>% t() %>% mean()
   x3.mean <- mids %>% map_df(~mean(.$SkinThickness)) %>% t() %>% mean()
   x4.mean <- mids %>% map_df(~mean(.$Insulin)) %>% t() %>% mean()
   
   #SE
   y.se <-  mids %>% map_df(~sd(.$BMI)) %>% t() %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(mids[[1]]))) %>% mean()
   x1.se <-  mids %>% map_df(~sd(.$Glucose)) %>% t() %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(mids[[1]]))) %>% mean()
   x2.se <-  mids %>% map_df(~sd(.$BloodPressure)) %>% t() %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(mids[[1]]))) %>% mean()
   x3.se <-  mids %>% map_df(~sd(.$SkinThickness)) %>% t() %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(mids[[1]]))) %>% mean()
   x4.se <-  mids %>% map_df(~sd(.$Insulin)) %>% t() %>% "/"(sqrt(nrow(mids[[1]]))) %>% mean()
   
   #Interval
   y.interval <- qt(.975, (nrow(mids[[1]]) - 1)) * y.se
   x1.interval <- qt(.975, (nrow(mids[[1]]) - 1)) * x1.se
   x2.interval <- qt(.975, (nrow(mids[[1]]) - 1)) * x2.se
   x3.interval <- qt(.975, (nrow(mids[[1]]) - 1)) * x3.se
   x4.interval <- qt(.975, (nrow(mids[[1]]) - 1)) * x4.se
   
   #lower
   y.lower <- y.mean - y.interval
   x1.lower <- x1.mean - x1.interval
   x2.lower <- x2.mean - x2.interval
   x3.lower <- x3.mean - x3.interval
   x4.lower <- x4.mean - x4.interval
   
   #upper
   y.upper  <- y.mean  +  y.interval
   x1.upper <- x1.mean + x1.interval
   x2.upper <- x2.mean + x2.interval
   x3.upper <- x3.mean + x3.interval
   x4.upper <- x4.mean + x4.interval   
   
   #aw
   y.aw <- y.upper - y.lower
   x1.aw <- x1.upper - x1.lower
   x2.aw <- x2.upper - x2.lower
   x3.aw <- x3.upper - x3.lower
   x4.aw <- x4.upper - x4.lower
   
   #Bias
   y.bias <- y.mean - y.true
   x1.bias <- x1.mean - x1.true
   x2.bias <- x2.mean - x2.true
   x3.bias <- x3.mean - x3.true
   x4.bias <- x4.mean - x4.true
   
   # Coverage rate
   y.coverage <- y.lower < y.true & y.true < y.upper
   x1.coverage <- x1.lower < x1.true & x1.true < x1.upper   
   x2.coverage <- x2.lower < x2.true & x2.true < x2.upper
   x3.coverage <- x3.lower < x3.true & x3.true < x3.upper
   x4.coverage <- x4.lower < x4.true & x4.true < x4.upper
   
   
  return(c(y.mean, y.se, y.aw, y.coverage, y.bias,
           x1.mean, x1.se, x1.aw, x1.coverage, x1.bias,
           x2.mean, x2.se, x2.aw, x2.coverage, x2.bias,
           x3.mean, x3.se, x3.aw, x3.coverage, x3.bias,
           x4.mean, x4.se, x4.aw, x4.coverage, x4.bias))
}

Function: results RMSE of imputations

grab.rmse <- function(x){
   
mean.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.mean.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
mean.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.mean.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
mean.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.mean.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
mean.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.mean.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
mean.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.mean.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.mean <- data.frame(y = mean.y, x1 = mean.x1, x2 = mean.x2, x3 = mean.x3, x4 = mean.x4) %>% cbind(., method='mean')

reg.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.reg.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
reg.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.reg.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
reg.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.reg.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
reg.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.reg.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
reg.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.reg.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.reg <- data.frame(y = reg.y, x1 = reg.x1, x2 = reg.x2, x3 = reg.x3, x4 = reg.x4) %>% cbind(., method='reg')

stochm1.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.stochm1.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm1.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm1.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm1.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm1.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm1.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm1.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm1.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm1.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.stochm1 <- data.frame(y = stochm1.y, x1 = stochm1.x1, x2 = stochm1.x2, x3 = stochm1.x3, x4 = stochm1.x4) %>% cbind(., method='stochm1')

stochm5.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.stochm5.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm5.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm5.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm5.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm5.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm5.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm5.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
stochm5.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.stochm5.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.stochm5 <- data.frame(y = stochm5.y, x1 = stochm5.x1, x2 = stochm5.x2, x3 = stochm5.x3, x4 = stochm5.x4) %>% cbind(., method='stochm5')

bayesm1.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.bayesm1.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm1.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm1.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm1.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm1.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm1.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm1.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm1.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm1.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.bayesm1 <- data.frame(y = bayesm1.y, x1 = bayesm1.x1, x2 = bayesm1.x2, x3 = bayesm1.x3, x4 = bayesm1.x4) %>% cbind(., method='bayesm1')

bayesm5.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.bayesm5.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm5.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm5.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm5.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm5.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm5.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm5.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
bayesm5.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.bayesm5.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.bayesm5 <- data.frame(y = bayesm5.y, x1 = bayesm5.x1, x2 = bayesm5.x2, x3 = bayesm5.x3, x4 = bayesm5.x4) %>% cbind(., method='bayesm5')

pmmm1.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.pmmm1.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm1.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm1.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm1.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm1.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm1.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm1.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm1.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm1.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.pmmm1 <- data.frame(y = pmmm1.y, x1 = pmmm1.x1, x2 = pmmm1.x2, x3 = pmmm1.x3, x4 = pmmm1.x4) %>% cbind(., method='pmmm1')

pmmm5.y <-  x %>% map("rmse.pmmm5.y") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm5.x1 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm5.x1") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm5.x2 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm5.x2") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm5.x3 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm5.x3") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
pmmm5.x4 <- x %>% map("rmse.pmmm5.x4") %>% as.data.frame() %>% t()
results.pmmm5 <- data.frame(y = pmmm5.y, x1 = pmmm5.x1, x2 = pmmm5.x2, x3 = pmmm5.x3, x4 = pmmm5.x4) %>% cbind(., method='pmmm5')

longformat_results <- rbind(results.mean, results.reg, results.stochm1, results.stochm5, results.bayesm1, results.bayesm5, results.pmmm1, results.pmmm5)

  return(longformat_results)
}

Plot: - RMSE of imputations

library(ggplot2)
library(reshape2)
library(gridExtra)

rmse.50$method <- factor(rmse.50$method,levels = c("mean", "reg", "bayesm1", "stochm1","pmmm1", "bayesm5", "stochm5", "pmmm5" ))

p1 <- ggplot(rmse.50, mapping=aes(x=method, y=y)) + 
  stat_boxplot(geom = "errorbar", width = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot() + labs(x = "Method", y = "RMSE BMI")

p2 <- ggplot(rmse.50, mapping=aes(x=method, y=x1)) + 
  stat_boxplot(geom = "errorbar", width = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot() + labs(x = "Method", y = "RMSE Glucose")

p3 <- ggplot(rmse.50, mapping=aes(x=method, y=x2)) + 
  stat_boxplot(geom = "errorbar", width = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot() + labs(x = "", y = "RMSE BloodPressure")

p4 <- ggplot(rmse.50, mapping=aes(x=method, y=x3)) + 
  stat_boxplot(geom = "errorbar", width = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot() + labs(x = "", y = "RMSE SkinThickness")

p5 <- ggplot(rmse.50, mapping=aes(x=method, y=x4)) + 
  stat_boxplot(geom = "errorbar", width = 0.2) + 
  geom_boxplot() + labs(x = "", y = "RMSE Insulin")

plot <- grid.arrange(p1 + theme_apa(), p2 + theme_apa(), p3 + theme_apa(), p4 + theme_apa(), p5 + theme_apa())

plot
